The lime here is reduced from the 1937 transcribed spec (2.5 oz) to 1 oz; the original as written reads as an unbalanced acid bomb, and Berry's c. 1953 Palm Springs revision uses similarly trimmed citrus.

In a #shaker{} combine @dark Jamaican rum{2.5%oz}, @fresh lime juice{1%oz}, @fresh lemon juice{0.5%oz}, @grenadine{0.5%oz}, and @Pernod{0.25%oz} with @crushed ice{1%cup}.
Shake hard until chilled.
Pour unstrained into a #12oz chimney glass{} and top with @soda water{1.5%oz}.
Garnish with a @mint sprig{1}.
